<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 25 at 6:58PM EDT until June 25 at 7:30PM EDT by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 730 PM EDT
FOR EASTERN SHIAWASSEE AND GENESEE COUNTIES...
At 658 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Grand Blanc,
moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
This severe storm will be near...
Davison around 715 PM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Atlas,
Juddville, Rankin, Thetford Township, Argentine, Genesee and Vernon.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
